  "_comment": "THE LOAD-BEARING PROOF (B0.1 grill#3): a faithful representation of the CURRENTLY SHIPPED infra/templates/project/hetzner plan — 2x hcloud_server (control-plane + worker) each with firewall_ids=[hcloud_firewall.this.id] (computed → unknown-until-apply), hcloud_network + subnet, hcloud_primary_ip, and hcloud_firewall.this with the exact rules from network.tf: world-open tcp 50000/50001 (Talos apid) + 6443 (k8s API), and intra-cluster tcp/udp/icmp scoped to the private CIDR. Expected: HCLOUD-FW-001 PASS (both servers reference the firewall), HCLOUD-NET-001 WARN (three world-open k8s/Talos ports, port 22 is NOT world-open), overall verdict=warn, ZERO fails. If this ever flips to fail, tonight's nightly bricks — that regression must break the build.",
